The paper discusses scaling up kernel methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. The focus is on large data sets, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the mention of neural networks and their popularity suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The use of optimization techniques and the mention of parallel execution settings suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the mention of empirical evidence and the use of classical kernel functions suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
